, affirmative action, and reparations for slavery and apartheid. The contributors also consider Sartre's impact upon the insurgent antiracist activists and writers who also walked the roads to freedom that Sartre helped pave.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aPhenomenological sociology. 0aRacism. 0aSociologyxPhilosophy. 4aArea Studies : French Studies. 4aCultural Studies : Cultural Critique. 4aCultural Studies : Postcolonial Studies. 4aHistory : Intellectual History. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 7aPHILOSOPHY / General.2bisacsh1 aArthur, Paige, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBernasconi, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aButler, Judith, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCiccariello-Maher, George, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDelacampagne, Christian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGordon, Lewis R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJudaken, Jonathan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJudaken, Jonathan, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMartinot, Steve, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMore, Mabogo P., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWatts, Richard H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978079147785440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780791477854423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780791477854/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2